### Summary

index.tsx's getServerSideProps isn't covered with tests yet, which is pulling down our coverage %:
![image](https://github.com/HHS/simpler-grants-gov/assets/25465464/680eb6c2-b107-4ea9-ad44-fe547d441cdf)

We want to write some tests for this to make sure props are being passed properly for server side rendering.


### Acceptance criteria

- [ ] Test Coverage for frontend/src/pages/index.tsx is 
![image](https://github.com/HHS/simpler-grants-gov/assets/25465464/b56b14a9-c2cd-43c6-bcf3-85e11f124cc8)

### Notes or Open Questions
- Consider whether this should ServerSideProps or StaticProps
-  Change this to getStaticProps if you're not using server-side rendering
export const getServerSideProps: GetServerSideProps = async ({ locale }) => {
  const translations = await serverSideTranslations(locale ?? "en");
  return { props: { ...translations } };
};

## Summary

Fixes #396

### Time to review: __5 mins__

## Changes proposed

- Updates text strings per approved content

## Context for reviewers

Components were developed with draft content. This PR updates them all to the latest approved content. 

## Additional information

I'm not sure if we should take a more robust snapshot of the index page content. I don't think we're using snapshots in this app yet, but we could do something like… 

```
  it("renders content", () => {
    const page = render(<Index />);

    expect(page).toMatchSnapshot();
  });
```

…tho that snaps quite a lot. Lemme know if you have thoughts.
